john mellor-crummey's home page




john mellor-crummey





in 1984, john mellor-crummey graduated magna cum laude from princeton university with a b.s.e. in electrical engineering and computer science. he continued his studies at the university of rochester, where he received the m.s. and ph.d. degrees in computer science in 1986 and 1989.  in 1989, he joined rice university as a research faculty fellow.  his research interests include programming environments for parallel processing, parallel algorithms, multiprocessor synchronization, operating systems, and parallel computer architectures.  dr. mellor-crummey is a member of acm.

for contact info, finger johnmc@cs.rice.edu.


